  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-11-18",
    "date": "2021-12-09T19:30:36Z",
    "text": "Court Legal Access and Student Support Act of 2021 or the CLASS Act of 2021\n\nThis bill prohibits institutions of higher education (IHEs) that participate in federal student-aid programs from restricting students' ability to pursue claims against IHEs in court. In addition, the bill makes mandatory arbitration agreements inapplicable to enrollment agreements between students and IHEs."
